    details: {
      problem: 'Nike\'s internal platform ecosystem consisted of 20+ applications built by different teams across regions. Each team had developed their own design patterns, component libraries, and styling approaches. This fragmentation created several critical problems: inconsistent user experiences confused employees switching between tools, designers spent 40% of their time recreating common UI patterns, engineers built duplicate components instead of reusing code, onboarding new team members took weeks due to lack of standards, and accessibility and usability issues were repeated across products. There was no single source of truth, and every new feature required starting from scratch.',
