      research: [
        'Audited UI patterns and components across all internal platforms',
        'Interviewed 40+ designers and engineers about pain points',
        'Analyzed design system adoption at companies like Airbnb, IBM, and Shopify',
        'Conducted workshops with product teams to define needs and priorities',
        'Studied accessibility standards (WCAG 2.1) and enterprise requirements',
        'Benchmarked against leading design systems (Material Design, Carbon, Polaris)'
      ],
      designProcess: [
        'Started with comprehensive audit of existing patterns and components',
        'Defined design principles and system architecture',
        'Created design token system for colors, typography, spacing, and elevation',
        'Designed foundational components (buttons, inputs, navigation, tables)',
        'Built more complex patterns (forms, data visualization, modals)',
        'Developed comprehensive documentation with usage guidelines and examples',
        'Collaborated with engineering on React implementation and API design',
        'Ran pilot projects with 3 teams to validate and refine the system',
        'Created contribution guidelines for teams to propose new components',
        'Established version control and release processes'
      ],
      keyDesignDecisions: [
        "**Token-first architecture over component-first:** Built design token system (colors, typography, spacing) before components. *Problem:* Component-first creates inconsistency and rework when themes change. *Alternatives:* Build components first (faster but inflexible), tokens later (causes rework), tokens-first (chosen). *Why:* Tokens provide single source of truth for styling — changes propagate automatically across all components. *Impact:* Enabled theming and reduced design-to-dev handoff by **50%**.",
        "**Pilot with 3 teams before full rollout:** Validated system with small pilot teams instead of immediate company-wide launch. *Problem:* Full rollout without validation risks failure at scale. *Alternatives:* Launch to everyone (high risk), slow waterfall approach (delayed value), pilot with 3 teams (chosen). *Why:* Pilots reveal real-world issues while limiting blast radius — feedback improves system before scale. *Impact:* Identified 15 critical improvements, enabling **85% adoption within 6 months**.",
        "**Open contribution model with governance:** Allowed teams to propose new components through defined process instead of closed system. *Problem:* Closed systems become bottlenecks and do not scale. *Alternatives:* Fully open (quality issues), fully closed (bottleneck), governed contribution (chosen). *Why:* Balances speed and quality — teams can contribute while maintaining standards. *Impact:* **40% efficiency improvement** and community ownership driving long-term sustainability.",
        "**Multi-tech-stack support (React + Angular + Figma):** Built design system for multiple stacks instead of React-only. *Problem:* Nike has legacy Angular apps that need consistency too. *Alternatives:* React-only (leaves Angular teams behind), wait for full migration (years), multi-stack support (chosen). *Why:* Pragmatic approach acknowledges reality of enterprise systems — enables consistency now, not after multi-year migration. *Impact:* Achieved **70% component duplication reduction** across all stacks."
      ],
      leadershipInfluence: [
        "Secured executive buy-in for design system investment by quantifying cost of fragmentation: designers spending 40% time on duplicate work = $2M+ annual waste, convincing leadership to fund initiative",
        "Influenced Engineering leadership to adopt token-first architecture by demonstrating CSS maintenance burden in existing apps — tokens reduce future technical debt by 60%",
        "Aligned 15+ product teams on pilot approach by showing Airbnb and Shopify case studies where pilot-driven systems achieved 2x faster adoption than top-down mandates",
        "Championed open contribution model by running workshop where teams proposed 12 components in 2 hours — proved community could drive system evolution with governance"
      ],
      beforeAfter: [
        "**Before:** 20+ fragmented apps, 40% designer time on duplicate work, 70% component duplication, 60% accessibility compliance, weeks to onboard new team members",
        "**After:** Unified design system, 40% efficiency improvement, 70% less duplication, 95% accessibility compliance, 60% faster onboarding, **10,000+ engineering hours saved annually**"
      ],
      finalSolution: 'The Enterprise Design System provides a comprehensive library of 60+ components, design tokens, patterns, and guidelines that enable teams to build consistent, accessible internal tools quickly. The system includes: a Figma component library for designers, a React component library for developers, comprehensive documentation with code examples, design tokens for theming and customization, accessibility built into every component, contribution processes for community involvement, and regular updates and maintenance. Teams can now build new features in days instead of weeks, with confidence that they\'re following Nike standards.',
      impact: [
        'Improved design and engineering efficiency by 40% across teams',
        'Reduced design-to-development handoff time by 50%',
        'Achieved 85% adoption rate across internal platform teams within 6 months',
        'Enabled 15+ product teams to ship features faster',
        'Reduced component duplication by 70%',
        'Improved accessibility compliance from 60% to 95%',
        'Decreased onboarding time for new designers and engineers by 60%',
        'Saved an estimated 10,000+ engineering hours annually through reuse',
        'Established foundation for scalable product development'
      ],
      learnings: [
        'Start small with foundational components before building complex patterns',
        'Documentation and examples are as important as the components themselves',
        'Governance and contribution processes drive long-term success',
        'Adoption requires ongoing evangelism, training, and support',
        'Balance consistency with flexibility for diverse use cases',
        'Measure impact through metrics, not just component count',
        'Collaborate closely with engineering from day one',
        'Build trust through quick wins before tackling complex migrations'
      ]
    }
