      research: [
        'Analyzed 10,000+ support tickets to identify common query patterns',
        'Interviewed 50+ employees about support pain points and expectations',
        'Shadowed support teams to understand workflows and edge cases',
        'Studied conversational AI patterns (ChatGPT, Intercom)',
        'Tested conversational prototypes with employees for usability',
        'Created personas for different employee support needs'
      ],
      designProcess: [
        'Mapped common employee questions and categorized by type',
        'Designed conversational interface with task-based structure',
        'Created guided response patterns instead of fully open-ended chat',
        'Prototyped LLM integration for natural language understanding',
        'Built escalation paths to human support with context handoff',
        'Tested with employees to validate usefulness and accuracy',
        'Designed feedback mechanisms to improve responses over time',
        'Created admin dashboard for performance monitoring',
        'Developed onboarding to introduce chat support to employees'
      ],
      keyDesignDecisions: [
        '**Guided responses over fully open-ended AI:** Decided to design structured, task-based responses instead of fully generative chat. *Problem:* Open-ended LLM can hallucinate or provide incorrect information with high confidence, risking employee trust. *Alternatives:* Fully open chat (high risk), keyword-based FAQ (inflexible), guided conversational paths (chosen). *Why:* Balances AI capability with accuracy and trust — LLM handles intent parsing while predefined responses ensure correctness. *Impact:* Achieved **82% accuracy rate** and **88% employee satisfaction** through guided structure.',
        '**LLM as intent parser, not source of truth:** Positioned LLM to understand user questions and route to appropriate responses, not generate answers from scratch. *Problem:* LLMs trained on public data lack Nike-specific platform knowledge, leading to generic or wrong answers. *Alternatives:* Fine-tune custom model (too expensive/slow), use RAG with internal docs (complexity), use intent-based routing (chosen). *Why:* Intent parsing requires less training data and is more reliable for enterprise use cases. *Impact:* Reduced implementation time by **6 weeks** and minimized hallucination risk.',
        '**Immediate escalation to human support:** Designed clear escalation path when AI could not confidently answer. *Problem:* Users lose trust if AI provides unhelpful answers with no exit. *Alternatives:* Force AI-only responses (breaks trust), ask users to file ticket separately (friction), seamless escalation with context (chosen). *Why:* Preserves trust while handling edge cases — humans receive full conversation context for efficient resolution. *Impact:* **65% query reduction** while maintaining trust for complex issues.',
        '**Slack-first integration over standalone app:** Launched in Slack (where employees already work) instead of building separate web app. *Problem:* Employees will not adopt another tool they need to remember and visit. *Alternatives:* Web-only app (low adoption), email-based (poor UX), Slack integration (chosen). *Why:* Meets users where they are, reduces adoption friction, enables quick access. *Impact:* Achieved **15,000+ conversations in 3 months** with minimal onboarding.'
      ],
      leadershipInfluence: [
