    overview: {
      context: 'Nike\'s CTO Office initiated a platform to visualize and navigate the technology organization\'s structure during a major restructuring. The goal was to help leadership and employees understand the new org chart, find colleagues, and identify reporting relationships across 10,000+ employees.',
      challenge: 'Leadership could not visualize or navigate the org structure at scale (1000+ nodes). Existing tools were static PDFs or outdated systems that couldn\'t handle complexity, causing 5+ minute search times and confusion during onboarding.',
      solution: 'Designed an enterprise org visualization platform with hierarchical graphs, cluster views, progressive disclosure, and powerful search. Worked directly with CTO office and engineering leadership to ensure scalability and performance.'
    },
    details: {
      problem: 'Nike\'s technology organization had   10,000+ employees   structured across complex hierarchies with   1000+ nodes  . During a major restructuring led by the CTO Office, leadership and employees struggled to understand the new org chart. Existing tools were static PDFs or legacy systems that couldn\'t visualize large-scale hierarchies. Finding a specific person took   5+ minutes  , new employees reported confusion during onboarding, and leadership lacked visibility into team structures. The system needed to handle   depth vs breadth   trade-offs while maintaining performance at scale.',
      roleResponsibilities: [
        'Partnered directly with CTO Office and engineering leadership',
        'Drove end-to-end UX design and information architecture',
        'Defined hierarchy rules and system structure: Departments → Teams → Roles → Individuals',
        'Designed progressive disclosure patterns for 1000+ node complexity',
        'Created clustering system for large org structures',
        'Built interaction flows for drill-down and cross-team navigation',
        'Designed node card system, connectors, and detail panels',
        'Ensured performance optimization at enterprise scale'
      ],
      constraints: [
        'Had to visualize 1000+ nodes without overwhelming users',
        'Balance depth vs breadth in hierarchy display',
        'Performance requirements for real-time rendering',
        'Privacy and permission controls for employee data',
        'Integration with HR systems and Active Directory',
        'Mobile and desktop optimization',
        'Tight timeline due to org restructuring urgency'
      ],
      research: [
        'Conducted discovery sessions with CTO Office to understand leadership needs',
        'Interviewed 40+ employees, managers, and executives about navigation pain points',
        'Analyzed existing org tools and static PDF usage patterns',
        'Studied enterprise org visualization tools (Workday, BambooHR)',
        'Tested information architecture with card sorting and tree testing',
        'Created mental models for hierarchy exploration and person discovery'
      ],
      designProcess: [
        'Started with CTO Office discovery to define business requirements',
        'Mapped system hierarchy: Departments → Teams → Roles → Individuals',
        'Designed hierarchy rules balancing depth and breadth',
        'Created progressive disclosure patterns (expand/collapse, grouping)',
        'Introduced clustering for large teams and departments',
        'Designed drill-down and cross-team navigation flows',
        'Built node card system with person details and connectors',
        'Designed filters, search, and discovery features',
        'Prototyped dark mode and visual styling for hierarchy graphs',
        'Tested with leadership and employees across multiple rounds'
      ],
      keyDesignDecisions: [
        "**Progressive disclosure over full visualization:** Decided to hide complexity by default and reveal on-demand instead of showing all 1000+ nodes. *Problem:* Full hierarchy overwhelmed users and caused performance issues. *Alternatives:* Show everything (poor performance, overwhelming), pagination (breaks mental model), progressive disclosure (chosen). *Why:* Users need context-appropriate detail — start simple, enable drill-down when needed. *Impact:* Achieved **80% faster navigation** and smooth performance with 1000+ nodes.",
        "**Clustering large teams over individual nodes:** Grouped teams with 15+ members into collapsible clusters instead of showing every person. *Problem:* Large teams created visual clutter and made structure unclear. *Alternatives:* Show all individuals (cluttered), hide large teams entirely (loses info), cluster with expand option (chosen). *Why:* Clustering preserves structure while reducing cognitive load — users can expand when they need detail. *Impact:* Improved comprehension and **50% onboarding clarity increase**.",
        "**Depth-first hierarchy (4 levels max) over breadth-first:** Designed system to prioritize vertical depth (Department → Team → Role → Individual) over horizontal breadth. *Problem:* Breadth-first creates wide, flat structures that are hard to scan. *Alternatives:* Flat hierarchy (loses context), unlimited depth (confusing), 4-level cap (chosen). *Why:* Depth provides context and reporting relationships — 4 levels balances detail with simplicity. *Impact:* Reduced person search time from **5 min → <30 sec**.",
        "**Real-time sync with HR systems over manual updates:** Integrated directly with Active Directory for live data instead of manual org chart updates. *Problem:* Static org charts become outdated immediately during restructuring. *Alternatives:* Manual updates (maintenance burden), weekly sync (stale data), real-time sync (chosen). *Why:* Restructuring requires trust in data accuracy — real-time updates maintain credibility. *Impact:* Enabled seamless org restructuring with **9,500+ active users** and **88% satisfaction**."
      ],
      leadershipInfluence: [
        "Convinced CTO Office to prioritize progressive disclosure over full visualization by demonstrating performance issues with 1000+ nodes in prototype — shifted strategy from ambitious scope to usable MVP",
        "Aligned Engineering on clustering algorithm by running user tests showing 70% comprehension improvement with clusters vs individual nodes, securing engineering investment",
        "Influenced HR and IT to enable real-time Active Directory integration by presenting org restructuring timeline risks — manual updates would lag by weeks, breaking trust",
        "Championed 8-week aggressive timeline by running rapid design sprints and weekly CTO reviews — delivered on-time for org restructuring announcement"
      ],
      beforeAfter: [
        "**Before:** Static PDFs, 5+ minute search times, no leadership visibility into org structure, confusion during onboarding, 1000+ node complexity unmanageable",
        "**After:** Interactive platform, <30 second search, real-time updates, 80% faster navigation, 50% onboarding clarity improvement, 9,500+ active users, 88% satisfaction"
      ],
      finalSolution: 'The Organization Hierarchy Platform provides:   Hierarchy Graph   with expandable/collapsible nodes showing Departments → Teams → Roles → Individuals;   Cluster View   that groups large teams for better visualization;   Node Card System   displaying employee info and reporting relationships;   Person Detail Panel   with contact info, role, and team context;   Progressive Disclosure   to manage 1000+ node complexity;   Powerful Search   with autocomplete and filters;   Cross-team Navigation   for exploring connections. The platform is optimized for performance at enterprise scale and includes dark mode support.',
      impact: [
        'Improved navigation speed by   80%   (from 5 minutes to under 1 minute)',
        'Reduced person search time from   5 minutes → <30 seconds  ',
        'Increased onboarding clarity by   50%   based on new hire feedback',
        'Supported   1000+ node   org structures with smooth performance',
        'Achieved   88%   user satisfaction among leadership and employees',
        'Enabled seamless org restructuring with real-time updates',
        '  9,500+ active users   within first 3 months of launch',
        'Reduced HR inquiries about org structure by   65%  '
      ],
      learnings: [
        'Progressive disclosure is critical for managing 1000+ node complexity',
        'Depth vs breadth trade-offs require careful hierarchy design rules',
        'Clustering large structures improves comprehension without losing detail',
        'Performance optimization at scale requires engineering collaboration from day one',
        'Leadership visibility drives org-wide adoption and usage',
        'Real-time updates are essential for maintaining trust during restructuring'
      ]
    }
  },

